{"id": 237074954, "title": "Meghan Markle and Prince Harry still \u2018very much in love\u2019 despite family tensions", "text": "As tension between Prince Harry and the royal family continues to simmer, one source of comfort the Duke of Sussex can undoubtedly rely on, is the support of his doting wife Meghan Markle. The couple, delighted fans last month when they visited Nigeria as part of an unofficial royal tour - with the couple candidly described as \u2018very much in love\u2019 by one of Meghan\u2019s former Suits co-stars. Speaking at this year\u2019s Tony Awards on Sunday evening, Wendell Pierce, 60 told PEOPLE that the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were \u201cvery much in love\u201d when he met up with the pair last year, even as the Prince\u2019s relationship remained strained with his other relatives. \u201cWhen [Meghan] came into town, she got an award last year, had a chance to say hello and wish she and Prince Harry well and wish the children well,\u201d Pierce told the publication. \u201cThey look very much in love and were very happy, so that's the most important thing.\" READ MORE: Meghan Markle sends more American Riviera jam to Prince Harry's pal after 'blow to brand' Wendell and Meghan previously shared a close bond after starring together on legal drama Suits until 2019, with Wendell playing the on-screen father of Meghan\u2019s character Rachel Zane. Describing working alongside her as \u201ca blast\u201d, he also revealed that since the show\u2019s conclusion he has kept in touch with the 42 year old Duchess and met up with her a few times. \u201cI've gotten to see her just a few times since, and we've been able to reminisce and so it's real, we have fond memories of working together,\u201d the Tony Award winner shared. During the same interview, Wendell also revealed that he had been \u201csurprised\u2019 by the show\u2019s resurgence in popularity last year, as a whole new generation of fans tuned into to watch the show from start to finish when it was added to streaming service Netflix. Following the boost in popularity, it was revealed earlier this year that a spinoff series would see fans return to the Suits universe, in Suits LA, led by Arrow actor Stephen Amell. There was even talk previously of whether or not the Duchess herself would be willing to return to the show and reprise her iconic role as Rachel Zane for a second time. Meghan also previously added further fuel to the fire about a possible return to the show, as she previously told Oprah Winfrey that she would \u201cnever say never\u201d to a return - something which was later also teased by former on-screen love interest Patrick Adams at this year\u2019s Golden Globes.", "summary": "The Duke and Duchess of Sussex are still 'very much in love' and 'very happy' despite their ongoing feud with the royal family, claims one of Meghan's former Suits co-stars", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/royals/meghan-markle-prince-harry-still-33051813", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article33035994.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_GettyImages-942614676.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-18 00:17:26", "author": "Phoebe Tonks", "authors": ["Phoebe Tonks"], "language": "en", "catgory": "entertainment", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.291}